File: Eskom asks customers to reduce demand by using electricity sparingly. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says stage 2 load-shedding is highly likely again this Wednesday evening. It's suspended power cuts for now, but says it will need to replenish water resources for its pumped storage schemes, and minimise the use of diesel at the open cycle gas turbines. READ: Eskom to implement Stage 2 load-shedding on Wednesday morning Eskom has confirmed  it is currently using diesel to meet electricity demands. The embattled power utility says the power system remains vulnerable. Eskom says it will keep customers informed of the status of the power system.